cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper deals with hate speech on social media, specifically Twitter, and uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the language used by hate speech instigators and targets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also analyzes the social and psychological aspects of hate speech, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The paper also deals with cyberbullying and online harassment, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
